
-- Insert the Twitter content into social_media_content table
INSERT INTO social_media_content (id, content_type, url, title, author_handle) VALUES 
(gen_random_uuid(), 'twitter', 'https://twitter.com/user/status/1952749610520478152', 'David danced with all his might to honour the Lord, and they brought the Covenant Box to Jerusalem with shouts of joy. (2 Sam:6/15) People may criticise our prayers, but when we adore and glorify God, He will make us a great person and save us from our enemies.', 'user'),
(gen_random_uuid(), 'twitter', 'https://twitter.com/user/status/1952225742038950224', 'David decided not to take the Covenant Box with him; instead, he took it to the house of Obed-Edom. God blessed Obed-Edom and his entire household. Gods word when we receive, He intervenes in our lives. Blessings will come upon every person — in their homes and in their lives.', 'user'),
(gen_random_uuid(), 'twitter', 'https://twitter.com/user/status/1952002498707050650', 'The Lord says, "I will condemn the person who turns away from me and puts his trust in man. Nothing good ever happens to him. But I will bless the person who puts his trust in me. He is like a tree growing near a stream; it continues to bear fruit." (Based on Jeremiah 17:5-8)', 'user'),
(gen_random_uuid(), 'twitter', 'https://twitter.com/user/status/1952000636104626466', 'For God loved the world so much that He gave His only Son, so that everyone who believes in Him may not perish but have eternal life. (John 3:16) Whoever believes and has faith in Him will never fail; His words lead us to success.', 'user'),
(gen_random_uuid(), 'twitter', 'https://twitter.com/user/status/1951496396986785978', 'God, Stretch out your hand to heal, and let signs and wonders be done After they prayed, the place shook, they were all filled with the Holy Spirit. Every word of God holds a store of blessings. Lord, stretch out Your hand over our problems, our health, and our prayers', 'user'),
(gen_random_uuid(), 'twitter', 'https://twitter.com/user/status/1951172908317024762', 'King Melchizedek, also a priest of the Most High God, brought bread and wine to Abram, blessed him and said, "May the Most High God bless Abram!" (Gen 14:18,29) When we pray, we should bless and say it aloud. The Bible says, when you bless, I too will bless.', 'user'),
(gen_random_uuid(), 'twitter', 'https://twitter.com/user/status/1950778965842706471', 'The widow went and did as Elijah told her; the bowl never ran out of flour, and the jar never ran out of oil. (1 Kings 17:15,16) When we obey God faithfully, we will see His hand at work. When we receive His word, today or tomorrow, His blessings will surely come upon us.', 'user'),
(gen_random_uuid(), 'twitter', 'https://twitter.com/user/status/1950774860856144001', 'The Israelites walked through the sea on dry ground, with walls of water on both sides (Exo 14) Moses raised his hands in prayer over the sea. God makes us walk on a clear path, not in the mud. Someone lifted their arms in prayer for us — thats why we are saved from our troubles', 'user'),
(gen_random_uuid(), 'twitter', 'https://twitter.com/user/status/1950038955136634970', 'Samuel thought, "This is the man the Lord has chosen." But God said, I have rejected him. Man looks at outward appearance, but I look at the heart. We must always seek Gods will. If we choose by our sight, it may lead to pain. Lets pray, "Lord, Your will be done in our lives.', 'user'),
(gen_random_uuid(), 'twitter', 'https://twitter.com/user/status/1949632710932300147', 'Samuel took the olive oil and anointed David. Immediately, the Spirit of the Lord took control of him and was with him from that day on. (1 Sam 16:13) When we have faith and believe, enemies disappear, problems break down, and Gods protection will always be upon us.', 'user'),
(gen_random_uuid(), 'twitter', 'https://twitter.com/user/status/1949630649784230084', 'A strong wind blew, waves spilled into the boat. Jesus was sleeping with his head on a pillow. The disciples woke him and said, "Teacher, dont you care we are about to die?" When we cry and pray, Jesus listens. He will rise for us, calm our storms, and bring peace into our lives', 'user'),
(gen_random_uuid(), 'twitter', 'https://twitter.com/user/status/1927969518623547886', 'Josephs dream "We were tying sheaves in the field. My sheaf stood upright, and yours bowed down to mine." Whatever God gives, Gods words and visions must be taken seriously. Joseph valued his dream—and it shaped his life. If we listen to God, He will bless us and lead us', 'user'),
(gen_random_uuid(), 'twitter', 'https://twitter.com/user/status/1927596438269096038', 'They heard the Lord walking in the garden… and hid among the trees. I was afraid because I was naked (Gen 3:8). God visits us—especially in hard times. Dont hide like Adam did. His voice means His presence. Stay in His sight. God shows up in tough times too', 'user'),
(gen_random_uuid(), 'twitter', 'https://twitter.com/user/status/1927241360559460574', 'He led me through the valley—it was full of dry bones. Lifeless. He asked, "Can these bones live?" (Ezekiel 37:1) Even when hope is gone, when we believe Him, His hand lifts us up like He breathed life into dry bones, He restore what looks dead', 'user'),
(gen_random_uuid(), 'twitter', 'https://twitter.com/user/status/1926873582564430077', 'I have made you a light for the Gentiles, that you may bring salvation to the ends of the earth. — Acts 13:47 Like lamps lit by Gods Word, we shine through our flaws. Though sinners, He lit me to bring light, we can shine for others. Seeds take time to bear fruit.', 'user'),
(gen_random_uuid(), 'twitter', 'https://twitter.com/user/status/1926513896262713559', 'Jesus crossed Galilee. A crowd followed Him. He asked Philip, Where can we buy food for them? He was testing him—Jesus already knew what He would do.(John 6:1–6) God has a plan for each of us, whoever follows Jesus, He knows when and how to bless us. Nothing is lost in His hands.', 'user'),
(gen_random_uuid(), 'twitter', 'https://twitter.com/user/status/1926169872548987052', 'Suddenly the Spirit of the Lord will take control of you, and you will become a different person. (1 Sam. 10:6) We are sinners. We fail. We lack many things, but when Gods Spirit moves, everything changes. He makes us new, and restores all we lost.', 'user'),
(gen_random_uuid(), 'twitter', 'https://twitter.com/user/status/1925817471329505594', 'you give food to the hungry and help those in need, your darkness will become as bright as noon. — Isaiah 58:10) When you comfort the hurting and help the needy, heaven moves. Your own struggles will fade, blessings will overflow, and Gods light will lead you into a new life.', 'user'),
(gen_random_uuid(), 'twitter', 'https://twitter.com/user/status/1925427378106638535', 'The Lord spoke to Moses face to face, like a friend, Joshua stayed with him. (Exo 33:11) he experienced gods presence god blessed Joshua that no one will be able to defeat you When we value and stay in Gods presence, we step into blessing and into our personal life too.', 'user'),
(gen_random_uuid(), 'twitter', 'https://twitter.com/user/status/1925057983140311107', 'Jesus took 5 loaves & 2 fish, looked to heaven, thanked God & a miracle followed (Luke 9:16). Like Him, lets give our worries to God, pray faithfully—He will hear us. Blessings will flow, and miracles can happen in our lives too.', 'user');

